Area Balance Review Checklist
=============================

Monsters
--------
__ Mobs are of appropriate toughness relative to overall area difficulty.
__ Mobs are of appropriate toughness relative to their own level.
__ Monster toughness is hinted at in descs if unexpectedly strong/weak.

Loot
----
__ Loot value (after selling) is appropriate to their owners' toughnesses.
__ Getting the loot requires appropriate level of risk/action.
__ Special items are not too powerful regardless of difficulty.
__ Concentration of exceptional and unique items meet current standards.
__ Loot should be enough to be an incentive for adventuring in the area.
__ The amount of cash loot is small compared to sellable loot.

Puzzles
-------
__ Puzzle difficulty is based on thought required, not syntax.
__ Loot acquisition is not based entirely on puzzles (access to monsters
   which carry the loot may be).
__ Puzzles should be reasonably solvable.

Traps
-----
__ Traps have lethality relative to the overall area difficulty.
__ Deathtraps should be avoidable if appropriate clues are heeded.


